<br>
1st - Goal:<br>
<br>
As several people have already said, The Sentinent's never really had a "goal" per se.  We all joined up wayyyy back when so that we could chat and keep tabs on friends when we weren't grouped together.  I think that we've kinda' continued along those lines.  I, personally, think that's a good thing.  It allows everyone to have fun and do your own thing.  If you want to go sit by Puntar and fish while other guildies are raiding, you're welcome to, and no-one's going to yell at you.  On the other hand, if you want to join up with some guildies for a night, you'll almost always be able to.<br>
<br>
2nd - Alts:<br>
<br>
This is something that the OC is discussing at the moment in regards to alts in other guilds (which I personally have no problem with, regardless of the other guild or alt's level/class), but we have had a lot of discussions on alts in the past.  Like a lot of previous posters, I've been through my "hell with this, let's make a newbie" phases.  Several times....like....A LOT.  :-)  For a while it was a running joke to see how many alts I had active at one time...  Through it all, despite the fact that they could have used a 'chanter (I was the only one in the guild back then), everyone supported me and let me have fun, and they still do when I play my alts.  I don't believe that this guild has ever really discouraged alts.  Anything like that which may have been seen in guild chat was, I'm sure, a joke.  Which brings me to....<br>
<br>
3rd - Level/Class invites:<br>
<br>
Ger'Mish (did I get it right?), as long as I have been in this guild, we have been unbalanced.  We have what, 25 people above 40 now?  And only 2 of them are clerics.  As I mentioned before, up until not too long ago, I was the ONLY enchanter, in a guild of like 40+ people.  We had ONE wizard, ONE rogue, etc...we've never been balanced.  Because of this, there are many times when we've said "Boy we sure could use another wizzie.." or warrior, or cleric, or what have you, but we have NEVER approved/denied admission to the guild based on this, and I firmly believe that we never will.  Also, just to clear up the Ranger thing....  You may have noticed that when we get a new recruit (almost every time..hehe), someone makes a crack about Rangers.  "Noooo, not another Ranger!"  "Whew, it's not a Ranger," etc.  If you pay attention, you'll notice that it's all us old-school Sentinenters saying this (Me, Gal, Taan, Valencia, Caedo, etc...).  This is an old old joke in the Sentinent, and does not reflect any bias or anything towards any classes.  For a while there a long time ago, it seemed like the only people that ever joined were rangers.  We had 1 cleric, 1 'chanter, 1 wizzie, etc....and 73 rangers.  ;-)  So it got to be kind of a running gag, nothing more.  Anyhoo, just wanted to clear that up, there's no evil intent there, it's just old guildies showing our age.  :-)<br>
<br>
Wow, this went on long...there's actually more that I'd like to post, but damn I turned out to be long-winded.  Guess I'll skip the other stuff...<br>
<br>
Teynor Sax<br>
47 Enchanter<br>
Proud Member of the Sentinent<br>
